{{Infobox football biography | name = Marius Aam | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1980|11|14|df=y}} | birth_place = | height = | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = defender | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Aalesunds FK|Aalesund]] | years1 = –2006 | clubs1 = [[Aalesunds FK|Aalesund]] | years2 = 2007–2008 | clubs2 = [[Skarbøvik IF|Skarbøvik]] | years3 = 2010 | clubs3 = [[Hessa IL|Hessa]] | years4 = 2014 | clubs4 = [[Skarbøvik IF|Skarbøvik]] | pcupdate = 8 June 2015 }} '''Marius Aam''' (born 14 November 1980) is a retired [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[football defender]] who notably played in [[Tippeligaen]] for [[Aalesunds FK|Aalesund]].
He started his career in Aalesund, and played first-tier fotball for them in Tippeligaen 2003 and 2005. He was not a first-team regular, and quit the team in early 2006.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aam gir seg i AaFK|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=4 May 2006|work=Aftenposten|page=27|language=Norwegian}}</ref> The next season, he fielded for [[Ålesund]]'s second best club at the time, [[Skarbøvik IF]].
Leaving Skarbøvik ahead of the 2009 season,<ref>{{cite news|title=SIF mister rutine|last=Lorgen|first=Gunnar|date=14 January 2009|work=Sunnmørsposten|page=21|language=Norwegian}}</ref> he later featured for sixth-tier club [[Hessa IL|Hessa]].<ref>{{cite news|title=5. divisjon i gang|last=Skuseth|first=Helge|date=13 April 2010|work=Sunnmørsposten|page=8|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He also made a comeback in Skarbøvik.<ref>{{cite news|title=Her kjem sportsredaksjonen i Vikebladet Vestposten sine tips|date=3 April 2014|work=Vikebladet Vestposten|pages=14–15|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
