{{Infobox person |name = Peter Andreevich Tkachev |image = |image_size = 200px |caption = |birth_date = |birth_place = |residence = |nationality = [[Russia]]n |known_for = Designer of the Balanced Automatic Recoil System (BARS) |occupation = Small arms designer, |spouse = |parents = |children = |awards = }}
'''Peter Andreevich Tkachev''' was a Russian weapons engineer for [[TsNIITochMash]]. He is known to have worked on and modifiy various weapons such as the [[AO-38 assault rifle|AO-38]], [[AO-46 (firearm)|AO-46]], AO-62 and AO-63 assault rifles as well as developing the [[Balanced Automatics Recoil System]] (BARS) used in the [[AK-107]].<ref>"Солдат удачи" номер 9 (72) 2000 Д.Ширяев "Кто изобрел автомат Калашникова"</ref>
